<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-04-16T14:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-04-16T14:00:00-05:00" n="330" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d330">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 658.119/312</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                    to the Ambassador in Great Britain</hi> (<persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_PWH1" type="to"><hi rend="italic">Page</hi></persName>)</head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                            </opener>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-04-16T15:00:00-04:00">
                                        <hi rend="italic">April 16, 1918, 3 p.m.</hi>
                                    </date>
                                </dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>7301. For <persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_SLP1">Sheldon</persName> [from War Trade Board]:</p>
                            <p>347. Embassy’s 9439, April 10, 7 p.m., your 404. Swedish <hi rend="italic">modus vivendi</hi>. Glad to learn list of 100,000
                                tons is practically complete allowing: the licensing of additional
                                rations for Sweden.</p>
                            <pb facs="0387" n="1221" xml:id="pg_1221"/>
                            <list>
                                <label>3.<note n="1" xml:id="d330fn1">This and following numbers
                                        refer to corresponding paragraph numbers in telegram of Apr.
                                        10.</note>
                                </label>
                                <item>Please give us names of the three ships which sailed from
                                    Sweden and stopped at Bergen.</item>
                                <label>4.</label>
                                <item>We are considering matter of phosphate rock and will let the
                                    10,000 tons clear if satisfactory assurances are given of
                                    chartering similar amount of tonnage for the period of four
                                    months as agreed.</item>
                                <label>6.</label>
                                <item>When will steamship <hi rend="italic">Alida</hi> sail from
                                    other side? This in order to arrange about fuel oil for
                                    her.</item>
                                <label>7.</label>
                                <item>Your understanding is correct. Fifty per cent division will
                                    apply to vessels chartered by United States and England under
                                    clause 3, same as clause 2. It should be borne in mind that
                                    England owes us large amount of tonnage still under Norwegian
                                    50-50 agreement and that this will be subject of discussion
                                    between <persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_FT1">Fisher</persName> and <persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_MFC1">Munson</persName> Monday.
                                    Result of this will be cabled to you.</item>
                            </list>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_LR1">
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi>
                                    </persName>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>